      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Back up registry artifacts and add migration backup gate",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Replace the stale GitHub artifact backup path with R2/S3-compatible registry artifact backups for hosted skill versions and plugin/package release artifacts.\n- Store a browsable restore catalog under `skills/` and `packages/` with per-version `_meta.json` files plus root `_index.json` files.\n- Keep publish-time backup async and non-fatal; failed writes are queued as retry jobs, and the cron drains retries only instead of scanning the full registry.\n- Add admin seed/backfill support through `registryArtifactBackups:seedRegistryArtifactBackups` for the initial historical population.\n- Add the ClawHub migration lifecycle skill with the manual Convex dashboard `Backup Now` gate before production dry run/apply.\n\n## Backup Shape\n\n- `skills/<owner>/<skill-slug>/_index.json`\n- `skills/<owner>/<skill-slug>/<version>/_meta.json`\n- `skills/<owner>/<skill-slug>/<version>/<skill files...>`\n- `packages/<owner>/<package-name>/_index.json`\n- `packages/<owner>/<package-name>/<version>/_meta.json`\n- `packages/<owner>/<package-name>/<version>/<artifact.tgz>`\n\nThe indexes preserve latest and historical restore lookup metadata without relying on object-store listing or Git history.\n\n## Operator Notes\n\nRequired Convex env:\n\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_R2_ACCOUNT_ID` or `REGISTRY_BACKUP_S3_ENDPOINT`\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_BUCKET`\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_ACCESS_KEY_ID`\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`\n\nOptional:\n\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_S3_REGION`\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_SKILLS_ROOT`\n- `REGISTRY_BACKUP_PACKAGES_ROOT`\n\nRecommended smoke after deploy:\n\n- Run a dry-run seed with a tiny batch.\n- Run a real seed with `batchSize: 1, maxBatches: 1`.\n- Inspect the R2 `_meta.json` and `_index.json` objects for one backed-up skill/package.\n- Start the controlled seed/backfill separately.\n\n## Review Follow-up\n\n`$autoreview` accepted three P2 findings and this revision fixes them:\n\n- Rename-only skill changes now enqueue a latest-version backup refresh.\n- Publish-time skill/package backup actions rehydrate current Convex state before writing, so stale scheduled args cannot corrupt latest/index metadata.\n- Same-owner soft-deleted skill restore now reactivates and refreshes an existing version instead of republishing a duplicate version.\n\nAlso removed the `_index.json` 1000-version cap so the current backup head remains a full restore catalog.\n\n## Proof\n\n```bash\nbunx vitest run convex/registryArtifactBackups.test.ts convex/registryArtifactRestore.test.ts convex/skills.ownership.test.ts convex/lib/registryArtifactBackup.test.ts\n# passed: 4 files, 42 tests\n\nCONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:small-squirrel-75 VITE_CONVEX_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3212 bunx convex codegen && bunx tsc --noEmit --pretty false\n# passed\n\nbun run ci:static\n# passed\n\ngit diff --check\n# passed\n\nAUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n# initial pass accepted 3 P2 findings listed above; fixes landed\n# final rerun inspected the patch, ran the focused tests and TypeScript, then hit a recursive nested `codex review --uncommitted` invocation from the autoreview skill before printing a clean summary; no actionable finding was emitted before the recursion was stopped\n```\n",
        "branch": "pe/claw-289-registry-backup-gate",
